The paper discusses deep learning methods for multi-source domain adaptation, which involves transferring knowledge from multiple labeled source domains to an unlabeled or sparsely labeled target domain. This topic is highly relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on deep learning methods and their application to image and video data, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
